UNITED STATES of America, Appellee, v. Harold E. WITTEMAN, Appellant. No. 148. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Nov. 6, 1933. Morris E. Packer, of Brooklyn, N. Y., for appellant. Howard W. Ameli, U. S. Atty., of Brooklyn, N. Y. (Herbert H. Kellogg, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Brooklyn, N. Y., and Maxwell Pames, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for the United States.

Before MANTON, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed.
